n.Label: Trade Exposure Amount
n.Description: The maximum unfunded commitment of a loan asset owned by the borrower or any amount an investor stands to lose in investment should the investment fail.

n.Label: Underlying Instrument ID
n.Description: A unique identifier  that can be assigned to an instrument.

n.Name: Instrument Maturity Date
n.Label: Maturity Date
n.Description: The final date on which an instrument must be repaid in total.

n.Name: Instrument Type
n.Label: Underlying Asset Type for Financial Instrument
n.Description: Different instrument types act as a guarantee for the clients to conclude their business at the right time.

n.Name: Market Value Price
n.Label: Market Value Price
n.Description: The price an asset would fetch in the market place or the value that an investment community gives to a particular equity or business.

n.Name: Notional Value Amount
n.Label: Gross Notional Amount
n.Description: Total underlying amount of a derivatives trade or total value of the position, which is a product of the market value and the leverage ratio.

n.Name: Rating Value
n.Label: Rating Value
n.Description: A value based on detailed financial analysis of financial history, typically relating to the ability to meet debt obligations.

n.Name: Stress Exposure Amount
n.Label: Stressed Expected Exposure (CVA)
n.Description: A magnitude of consquences experienced from a possible disruption (stress scenario).

n.Name: Stress Scenario Value
n.Label: Stress Scenario Value
n.Description: Worth or usefulness of analysing a wide range of plausable scenarios that could adversly impact business continuity at different levels if the entity failed to respond appropriately.
